      "span_text": "To test this hypothesis, an emerging technique in cognitive neuroscience was used; functional transcranial Doppler (fTCD) ultrasound. fTCD assesses the relative changes in cerebral blood flow volume (CBFV) in each hemisphere, whilst participants undertake a cognitive task and has been shown to reliably detect activation in speech paradigms"
